{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_rigoletto_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608774/1958052901/1147.xml":{"full_text":"THE EVENINO STAR. Washington, D. C.\nTMINMYAY W4V 44. 1644\nA-18\nSavings, Loan Leaders\nLeave for Atlantic City\nBv DONALD B. HADLEY\n6t\u00abr riniotcltl Ultor\nExecutive! of 29 Washington laving* and loan association*\nand their guest* left today for the 50th annual meeting of the\nDiktrict Savings and Loan League at Hotel Claridge in Atlantic\nCl\u00bby N J.\nThe general business outlook, civic affairs and savings and\nloan problems will be given attention at morning business ses-\nMon* tomorrow and Saturday.\nOolf and other sport* will oc\ncupy the afternoons The an\nnual election la scheduled Sat\nurday.\nAround 240 executives and\ntheir auests are expected for\nthe sessions. Among the league\nveterans attending will be P.\nWillson Camp, executive vice\npresident of District Building\nand Loan Association, who is\nslated to be elected for his 21st\nterm as league secretary. An\nother is Robert E. Buckley,\npresident of National Perma\nnent Savings and Loan Asso\nciation. who is unopposed for\nhis 17th term as league treas\nurer.\nThe league's outgoing presi\ndent, Joseph P. Burke. Jr., vice\npresident of Columbia Federal\nSavings and Loan Association,\nand the executive secretary.\nBruce Bryan, will give their\nannual reports at tomorrow\u2019s\nsession. Quest speaker will be\nJoseph Holzka. president of the\nUnited States Savings and Loan\nLeague, with which the District\nassociations also are affiliated.\nStephen Q. Slipher. staff vice\npresident of the United States\nleague in charge of its Wash\nington office, will moderate a\npanel discussion of the busi\nness outlook later on In the\nsame session.\nPanel members will include:\nW. Franklin Morrison, execu\ntive vice president of First Fed\neral Savings Sc Loan Associa\ntion .and president of the Na\ntional Savings and Loan\nLeague; John A. O'Brien, as\nsistant general manager. Fed\neral Savings and Loan Insur\nance Corp.; Everett Smith, fis\ncal agent for Federal Home\nLoan Bank System, and F.\nWallace Stoever, vice president\nand real estate officer of Mun\nsey Trust Co.\nCapital Bank Deposits\n7 Pet. Above Vear Ago\nDeposits of 10 reserve mem\nber banks here amounted to\n$1,260,620,000 on May 21. a\ngain of *86,217.000 or 7.1 per\ncent from $1,194,403,000 on\nMay 22 last year, the weekly\nreport from the Federal Re\nserve Bank of Richmond dis\nclosed today.\nHowever, the latest total was\ndown $20,688,000 from *1,281,-\n288.000 a week earlier. The\nmember bank total constitutes\na large part of the over-all\nvolume of Washington\u2019s 15\nbanks and trust companies.\nDemand deposits amounted\nto $947,014,000 on May 21. up\n$23,277,000 from a year ago,\ndespite a decrease of $35,027.-\n000 from a week earlier. Time\ndeposits totaled *313.606 000. a\ngain of $42 940,000 from a year\njMUTUAL FU~NDS~\n(Vr\u00abtrril\u00bbt s O tat'ona.\nNIW YORK. e\u00ab* TV Natuml MSI\nCiitxs Securities Eeteirs. Inc\nNooji Quotations)\nBit AskM lit tsket\ntltrta Tint I M 111 Fount Ft 534 it 77\nAlfilU Ft 1.13 I N Crrotk Ft I.\u00abS It M\nBut Bw St I K 4.3$ income F Ml Ml\nAn Mu Ft 7.11 132 mint Fnt It N 12.81\ntill Ft Tr 131 111 Inti Bn Ft 113 IN\nAt.\" DMu 4.M 4 M ln\u00ab Cl Im Ml I.IT\nAi HFt 4 I K 5.51 lit Tr Hit Ml tl.ll\n\u00abi NFt I 741 111 Util Fnnt \u00bbM MM\nAx HSt Ft 117 I N Illusion 1114 11.14\nAx lei A tl Mi 11.51 KEYSTONE:\nAx ton Cn 22.52 24.81 Cnst 11 25 W2l 71\n\u25a0l\u00dfttMn 11111145 Cnst B 7 21 21 24.11\nBt II TAm 11.71 21.24 Cult 11 15.71 17 IS\nItslM Ft 71.14 11.11 Cnst I 4 lit 10 12\n\u25a0rt 11 Inn 21.12 2111 Cust B 1 MS Ml\n\u2022nllick Ft 11 IT 12 M Cnst K 2 It 21 11.17\nCalif Fnnt 7.12 7.71 Cust SI 14 it 11.11\nCm Sen Ft 17.11 1111 Cusl 1 2 11.1111.01\nCnuill Ft 1112 1121 Cust SI 11.11 11. H\nCtnlntGi 704 Til Cust S 4 103 177\nCut St It 22 M 23 17 Full Cm It 71 17.17\nCkiacl Ft 1111 17 It Knickcr Ft 111 117\nCnlMiti Ft IN 171 KuickStkF 4SI 142\n